The global economy continues to face multiple challenges as a result of the COVID-19 pandemic. The spotlight is on industrial digitalization as one of the pathways to providing a fresh impetus to economic revival. The scale of China's digital economy is $7 trillion, and 90 percent of it is associated with the real economy. How do technologies like AI and 5G empower digital transformation of the real economy? What are new opportunities after the ChatGPT moment? How to promote the digital development of industry and empower the real economy? Tom Mitchell, the Founders University Professor atÂ Carnegie Mellon University, and Zhang Yunyong, secretary of the Party Committee of China Unicom Yunnan Branch, and member of the 13th National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, offer some answers.